== Scallion Rice ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a small pot over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites and cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup} and @water{1 1/4%cups}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Salsa Fresca ==

While rice cooks, finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}(finely diced).

Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1}(core, deseeded, and diced into 1/2-inch pieces).

Drain and rinse @Black Beans{13.4%oz}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine tomato, half the scallion greens, and a large
drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Season generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

In a second small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tbsp} with @Southwest Spice Blend{1/2%tsp}.
Add @Water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

> You'll use the remaining Southwest Spice later.

== Bean Mixture ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add poblano
and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned,
~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Reduce heat to medium.

Stir beans, remaining @Southwest Spice Blend{1/2%tbsp}, and @Butter{1%tbsp} into
pan with poblano. Cook, stirring, until mixture is fragrant and butter has
melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Green Salsa{7.06%oz} and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until beans are softened, ~{1-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off
heat.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with bean mixture, @Pepper Jack Cheese{1/2%cup},
salsa fresca, and crema. Garnish with remaining scallion greens and serve.